HEADWORD: Mannide
<hw>Man"nide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Mann</ets>ite +
anhydr<ets>ide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white amorphous
or crystalline substance, obtained by dehydration of mannite, and
distinct from, but convertible into, mannitan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

